SetDevices

public int SetDevices(int Flags,
                      int numDsts,
                      Device[] DestList,
                      AS_Storage_EventListener.VolumeEventListener callback,
                      java.lang.Object userData)
Assigns a list of devices to be used by the specified volume. Each device must contain media of the same type and be either blank or re-writable. Re-writable media will be overwritten with no warning. It is the responsibility of the host application to ensure that re-writable media is either 'blank' or can be safely overwritten. Only volumes mounted for create (AS_Volume_Create or AS_Format_Create) may use this method. Volumes mounted on media with pre-existing data (AS_Volume_Mount) may not as their filesystem data is not transferable to the new device.
